
Required input data needs to be downloaded from figshare (see our GitHub page). 
As this is not possible without authenticating to figshare, we encourage the user to manually download the required files. 

Upon downloading meta-data, files need to be positioned in the correct directories in order for the codes to work.
The directory should be set up like this (* indicates a meta-data file that should be downloaded and moved to the directory):

-- Input
-- -- DCA_adjusted_matrix
-- -- -- *mean.tsv*
-- -- -- *latent.tsv*
-- -- Drugs
-- -- -- *drugs_w_indication_RA_DrugBank_20200214.txt*
-- -- -- *drug_targets_unique_literature_ppi.txt*
-- -- -- *drugs_with_identical_drug_target_combinations_literature_PPI.txt*
-- -- -- *all_drug_targets_drug_bank.txt*
-- -- GWAScat
-- -- -- *GWAS_RA_P_smaller_1e-8.txt*
-- -- mouse_homologs
-- -- -- *transl.txt*
-- -- literature_PPI
-- -- -- *ppi.txt*
-- -- Marker_genes
-- -- -- *Markers_for_cell_typing_heatmap_RA.txt*
-- R
-- -- *R codes from GitHub*
-- Output
-- -- FC_criteria_checking
-- -- -- *SUMMARY_only_drugs_passing_network_criteria_evaluated.txt*
-- -- Final_ranking
-- -- -- *FINAL_drug_ranking_evaluated.txt*
-- -- -- *FINAL_drug_ranking_evaluated.xlsx*

This can be done by running the first lines in the MAIN.R file before tranfering downloaded data to the appropriate directories.

R codes (from GitHub) should be deposit in the "your_file_path/R" directory, which also should be made the working directory.
